The '''R4-P astromech droid''' was a truncated [[Industrial Automaton/Legends|Industrial Automaton]] [[R4 astromech droid/Legends|R4-series astromech droid]] incorporated into the [[Delta-7 Aethersprite-class light interceptor/Legends|Delta-7 ''Aethersprite''-class light interceptors]] of the [[Jedi Order/Legends|Jedi Order]],<ref name="FF62" /> which had fuselages too slim to house full-sized [[Astromech droid/Legends|astromech droids]].<ref name="R4-P">{{CSWECite|III|113|R4-P}}</ref> 

Based upon [[Anakin Skywalker/Legends|Anakin Skywalker's]] alterations to [[R4-P17/Legends|R4-P17]],<ref name="FF62" /> they were modified by [[Kuat Systems Engineering/Legends|Kuat Systems Engineering]]<ref name="State of the Arts" /> to feature the dome of an [[R2-series astromech droid/Legends|R2-series astromech droid]] in place of the conical head of an R4 unit, creating what was essentially a hybrid of the two models.<ref name="FF62" /> 

As a result, the R4-P could store up to ten sets of [[Hyperspace/Legends|hyperspace]] jump coordinates in its memory,<ref name="SotG">[[Starships of the Galaxy (Saga Edition)|''Starships of the Galaxy'', Saga Edition]]</ref> rather than the single jump of a standard R4 unit.<ref name="TNEGtD" /> When the [[Delta-7B Aethersprite-class light interceptor/Legends|Delta-7B ''Aethersprite''-class light interceptor]] gained popularity, many R4-Ps were retrofitted with standard-sized astromech bodies.<ref name="R4-P" />

